description: Take a trip and witness the rise and fall of Tim Scully and Nicholas Sand, improbable pioneers of the drug counterculture during the 1960s.

title: The Surrounding Game
description: Teens in America dedicate themselves to the Asian game of Go, which originated in ancient China, drawing meaningful life lessons along the way.

title: The Tigers of Scotland
description: This documentary highlights the endangered existence of the Scottish wildcats, and the conservation efforts required to prevent their extinction.

title: The Truth About Alcohol
description: Emergency room doctor Javid Abdelmoneim endeavors to learn the truth about alcohol, both its benefits and risks, by exploring the science of drinking.

title: The Unknown Known
description: Donald Rumsfeld reviews his long political career, from his time in Congress to serving as secretary of defense under Gerald Ford and George W. Bush.

title: The Women Who Kill Lions
description: Experience an up-close look at the controversial passion and resulting infamy of big-game hunters Rebecca Francis and Jacine Jadresko.

title: The World's Most Wanted Animal
description: A conservationist shares her emotional journey in helping save rare, scaly mammals that have been illegally trafficked and now face extinction.

title: Theater of Life
description: This documentary follows chef Massimo Bottura as he opens a soup kitchen to cook gourmet meals for the needy from food waste at the 2015 Milan Expo.

title: Thelonious Monk: Straight, No Chaser
description: The spotlight shines on iconic jazz pianist and composer Thelonious Monk in this 1988 documentary featuring vintage performance clips and interviews.

title: This Was Tomorrow
description: The Tomorrowland music festival marks its 10th anniversary in Belgium, the U.S. and Brazil, with all the diverse excitement of the annual event.

title: Thunderbolt
description: A P-47 Thunderbolt squadron is shown in preparation, at play and in bombing raids aiming to halt Nazi supply lines and aid Allied ground troops.

title: To Be a Miss
director: Edward Ellis, Flor Salcedo, Aaron Woolf
description: Explore how the media and nationalism have fueled Venezuela's passion for physical appearance and the multibillion-dollar beauty pageant industry.

title: Tokyo Idols
description: This documentary follows J-Pop idol Rio and her predominantly middle-aged fans, and their seemingly transactional interactions.

title: Treasures from the Wreck of the Unbelievable
description: This cinematic journey into the waters off East Africa chronicles the story behind artist Damien Hirst's massive exhibition of oceanic treasures.

title: Tree Man
description: Entrepreneurs from Vermont and Quebec sell Christmas trees on the streets of New York, becoming a cherished part of neighborhood holiday traditions.

title: Trixie Mattel: Moving Parts
description: Drag queen Trixie Mattel deals with the bittersweet reality of success in this documentary that explores her rise to fame and subsequent music career.

title: Trophy
country: United Kingdom, Namibia, South Africa, Zimbabwe, United States
description: This documentary explores the tensions between the lucrative big-game hunting business and wildlife conservation from a variety of perspectives.

title: Tunisian Victory
director: Frank Capra, John Huston, Hugh Stewart, Roy Boulting, Anthony Veiller
description: British and American troops join forces to liberate a Nazi stranglehold in North Africa, sharing battles, hard work and a peaceful Christmas dinner.

title: Twice
description: This documentary reenacts the experiences of late activist Tsutomu Yamaguchi, a survivor of both atomic bombings on Japan in 1945.

title: Tyke Elephant Outlaw
description: This documentary recounts a 1994 incident in Honolulu in which a circus elephant attacked and killed its trainer, then ran loose on the city streets.

title: Tyson
description: In this surprisingly emotional documentary, heavyweight champ Mike Tyson analyzes the controversies surrounding his career and turbulent private life.

title: Unacknowledged
description: Noted UFO expert Dr. Steven Greer interviews witnesses and presents classified documents concerning the existence of extraterrestrials.

title: Under an Arctic Sky
casts: Chris Burkard, Sam Hammer, Heidar Logi, Elli Thor Magnusson, Ingo Olsen, Timmy Reyes, Justin Quintal, Steve Hawk, Sigurdur Jonsson, Mark Renneker
description: Six fearless surfers travel to the north coast of Iceland to ride waves unlike anything they've ever experienced, captured with high-tech cameras.

title: Undercover: How to Operate Behind Enemy Lines
description: This World War II-era training film dramatizes how secret agents should act while undercover and how to avoid capture by enemies.

title: Vegas Baby
description: A Las Vegas doctor's controversial online contest sees anxious entrants vie for free in vitro fertilization, a procedure rarely covered by insurance.

title: Vikings Unearthed
description: Archaeologist Sarah Parcak follows clues to early Viking explorations and discusses just what these notoriously fierce warriors were really like.

title: Walk with Me
description: A community of monks in France led by Zen Buddhist master Thich Nhat Hanh offers an intimate glimpse into mindfulness practice and the monastic life.

title: Water & Power: A California Heist
description: California residents and farmers face powerful barons in the struggle to secure water rights in this fresh historical account of profit and interests.

title: Waterschool
country: United States, Brazil, India, Uganda, China
description: Six young women, who each live near one of Earth's major rivers, share how the Waterschool environmental education program has impacted their lives.

title: We, the Marines
description: Narrated by actor and former Marine Gene Hackman, this documentary showcases the experience of becoming a member of the US Marine Corps.

title: Westside vs. the World
description: A look into the journey of influential strength coach Louie Simmons and the Westside Barbell gym he founded, evolving the sport of powerlifting.

title: What Makes a Psychopath?
description: This wide-ranging documentary examines the behaviors considered in a diagnosis of psychopathy and includes nonviolent, successful figures in history.

title: When Hari Got Married
description: A small-town taxi driver is arranged to be married, resulting in an intimate look at the clash between modernity and tradition in India.

title: When Two Worlds Collide
description: This documentary takes a hard look at how indigenous peoples clashed violently with the Peruvian government over land and economics in the Amazon.

title: Who the F**k Is That Guy?
description: Take a ride through the life of record exec Michael Alago, a gay Puerto Rican New Yorker who signed a slew of musical acts, including Metallica.

title: Why Are We Getting So Fat?
description: A Cambridge geneticist dispels misconceptions about living with obesity and explores why the epidemic continues to expand across the UK and America.

title: Why Knot
country: Canada, India, Thailand, United States, United Arab Emirates
description: Pressured by his traditional family to marry, a filmmaker explores the idea of monogamy and the possibility of lifelong union without sexual fidelity.

title: Why We Fight: The Battle of Russia
description: This installment of Frank Capra's acclaimed documentary series highlights the need for a Russo-American alliance to defeat the Nazis.

title: Williams
description: This inspiring documentary charts the birth of Sir Frank Williams's renowned racing empire – and the near-fatal crash that nearly stalled its future.

title: Winnie
description: Winnie Mandela speaks about her extraordinary and controversial career, from her early life to her marriage to her ongoing efforts to end apartheid.

title: Woodstock
description: For the 50th anniversary of the legendary Woodstock festival, organizers and attendees reminisce about one of the defining moments of the 1960s.

title: WWII: Report from the Aleutians
description: Filmmaker John Huston narrates this Oscar-nominated World War II-era film about life among the U.S. soldiers protecting Alaska’s Aleutian Islands.
